==English==
===Etymology===
A twentieth-century representation of Old English [[wicca|wiċċa]], in the mistaken belief that it was so pronounced.

===Pronunciation===
*IPA: /wɪkə/
*SAMPA: /wIk@/

===Homophones===
* [[wicker]] (''in non-[[rhotic]] dialects'')

===Noun===
# A modern pagan religion.
#: ''Wicca shares a number of elements with other religions.''

